College Loans 101
College loans are designed to cover the gap between cost of attendance and other financial aid. Here are some resources about how to get student loans for college. Learn about the differences between private and federal loans and how to evaluate the best college loan option for you.


















A Guide To Evaluating Student Loans
When evaluating student loan options, we encourage you to consider several factors.
















Consider Federal Student Loans
Federal student loans, are designed to cover the gap between cost of attendance and other financial aid.


















What Determines Your Private Student Loan Interest Rate
Understanding what determines rates for private student loans can help you make an informed borrowing decision. Learn more about what determines interest rates.


June 22, 2017|Louis DeNicola














How to Make Student Loan Payments While You're Still in School
You can save money on your student loan by making payments while you're still in school. Learn more about lowering the overall cost of your loan. 


December 8, 2016|Ashley Eneriz














How to Avoid Being Victimized By a Student Loan Scam
Many people have been receiving calls and emails about reducing or forgiving student loans. Here are some tips so you don’t fall victim to a student loan scam. 


November 3, 2016|Amanda Reaume














Credit Strategies for Cosigning a Student Loan
Before you cosign a college loan, learn more about how cosigning a student loan will affect a cosigner’s own credit.


October 20, 2016|Janet Berry-Johnson














How Bar Exam Loans Help Law Graduates
A bar exam loan can help by providing financial support while students prepare for this necessary next step in their legal careers.


June 23, 2016














What Do Student Loans Cover?
Here are some typical expenses that student loans can help cover. 















5 Things to Do Before Taking Out a Student Loan
Student loans are one source of money for school, but you also should consider other options. Here are steps to take before you commit to a college loan.















Understanding Student Loan Interest Rates
The interest rate is an important factor to compare because the interest rate affects the total cost of your loan.















The College Loan Application Process
Federal and private student loans have different application processes.















Compare Private Student Loans
Consider these features when researching loans for college.















Determine How Much to Borrow
You will need to figure out how much money to borrow in college loans once you have exhausted all other financial aid options















Direct Stafford Loans
Learn what are Direct Stafford Loans and the features of subsidized and unsubsidized federal loans.















Five Things You Should Pay for With Student Loans (And 5 You Shouldn’t)
Learn what you can pay for using a student loan. Find useful tips on what can you use a student loan for and what your student loan should not cover.















Top 10 Ways to Graduate with less debt
Learn how to keep your student loan debt to a minimum with 10 helpful tips.















How to Save on Your Student Loan
Learn how to save money on your student loan by exploring different repayment options from Discover Student Loans.















Average Annual Cost of College
Learn about the cost of a college education and how college choice might affect the average annual costs.













